<p class="govuk-body">This pattern lets the user change the language used in a service from English to Welsh and from Welsh to English.</p>

<h2 id="when-to-use" class="govuk-heading-l">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Use the Welsh language toggle when a service is available in Welsh.</p>

<h2 id="when-not-to-use" class="govuk-heading-l">When not to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Do not use the Welsh language toggle:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>where there is no Welsh translation for a service</li>
  <li>in personal tax account services – use the <a class="govuk-link" href="/design-library/account-header">account header</a> which already has a Welsh language toggle</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="how-it-works" class="govuk-heading-l">How it works</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">There are 2 ways to use the account header. You can use HTML or, if you are using Nunjucks or <a class="govuk-link" href="https://govuk-prototype-kit.herokuapp.com">version 7 or later of the GOV.UK Prototype Kit</a>, you can use the Nunjucks macro.</p>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  You need HMRC Frontend to use this pattern – <a class="govuk-link" href="/hmrc-design-patterns/install-hmrc-frontend-in-your-prototype/">find out how to install HMRC Frontend</a>. If you use the HMRC Nunjucks macro, you must copy and paste the entire macro in to your code.
</div>

<p class="govuk-body">Put the Welsh language toggle on the right hand side below the <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/header/">GOV.UK header</a>.</p>

